JMC Notes 0707

OOP:

- 'this' uses current object context or 'host' object
- 'new' constructor/operator.  Creates new instance of the object
- Pascal naming convention for object constructors; an object used
  with 'new'.  ex) var rian = new Student()

Inheritance:

1) set prototype of sublcass to parent class
   ex) Snake.prototype = new Animal();
2) invoke the constructor of superclass with
   context of 'this'
   ex) Animal.call(this,name);
3) set the constructor property
   ex) Snake.prototype.constructor = Snake;
